<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xml:id="_group__x_stream_buffer_spaces_available" xml:lang="en-US">
<title>xStreamBufferSpacesAvailable</title>
<indexterm><primary>xStreamBufferSpacesAvailable</primary></indexterm>

<para><link linkend="_stream__buffer_8h">stream_buffer.h</link></para>

<para><literallayout>
size_t <link linkend="_stream__buffer_8h_1a9a78e0206cb1dc343c329f9db579208d">xStreamBufferSpacesAvailable( StreamBufferHandle_t xStreamBuffer )</link>;
</literallayout></para>

<para>Queries a stream buffer to see how much free space it contains, which is equal to the amount of data that can be sent to the stream buffer before it is full.</para>

<para>
                <formalpara>
                    <title>
Parameters</title>
                    <para>
                    <table frame="all">
                        <tgroup cols="2" align="left" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                        <colspec colwidth="1*"/>
                        <colspec colwidth="4*"/>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
<entry>xStreamBuffer</entry><entry>
<para>The handle of the stream buffer being queried.</para>
</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                    </para>
                </formalpara>
                <formalpara><title>Returns</title>

<para>The number of bytes that can be written to the stream buffer before the stream buffer would be full. </para>
</formalpara>
</para>
